  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM humanitarian response in Mozambique, following the passage of the devastating tropican cyclone &#x201C;Idai&#x201D;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to provide humanitarian assistance to populations affected by Cyclone Idai in Mozambique. Especially, IOM is providing shelter kits, non-food items and hygiene kits to affected households while ensuring proper site facilitation/site decommissioning in IOM established displacement sites and supporting the government of Mozambique to facilitate return and relocation of the displaced population. It will also support the regular tracking of population movements into and out of displacement sites as well as monitor their needs through the expansion of the Displacement Tracking Matrix. While mainstreaming protection across sectors, IOM is also providing psychosocial support; assisting vulnerable persons with health care needs with transfer and referrals.</narrative>
  </description>
